launch.name: Starlink-27 (v1.0)
launch.details: This mission launches the 26th batch of operational Starlink satellites, which are version 1.0, from SLC-40. It is the 27th Starlink launch overall. The satellites will be delivered to low Earth orbit and will spend a few weeks maneuvering to their operational altitude. The booster is expected to land on an ASDS.
